<br>
Maybe lots of the d00ds wouldn't be d00ds if they had a better education about preferred practices of roleplay.  My education about Everquest comes from playing on other servers.  I certainly don't want to be known as Anradan &quot;the d00d&quot; of Firiona Vie.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Is there any time /shout is justified, or is it just generally frowned upon?<br>
<br>
I don't know how many people who play on Firiona Vie take the trouble to read a forum like this, and so might never know they were diminishing the experience of other people.<br>
<br>
It's too bad there aren't &quot;10 tenets&quot; of roleplay posted  somewhere in the cities.  It would be nice to somehow preserve the spirit of Firiona Vie.<br>
<br>
I'm really glad there is a community like this to participate in.  Thanks to you all.<br>
<br>
Anradan 11th season Wizard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uanradan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anradan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 1:04:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2790.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Whoops</span><hr size=1> Sorry I missed the thread on shouting down the list. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucaillougna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 524<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 1:07:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2790.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shouting  d00ds</span><hr size=1> Conventions of shout....  <br>
<br>
(( OOC: Think about where or how you would shout in real life... ))<br>
<br>
Would you shout a conversation across a mile or more?  Wouldn't you get a bit hoarse doing so?<br>
<br>
Would you shout personal intimate details (such as increases in you prowess or where you are presently located)?  What if your enemies might be listening and evaluating you?<br>
<br>
Would you shout to find out if someone has information you are looking for?  <br>
<br>
Would you shout because you want to proclaim a victory or other achievement?<br>
<br>
Would you shout because you noticed someone was in the same area but out of the distance of your speaking voice but still wanted to draw their attention?<br>
<br>
Would you shout to warn people of an impending disaster ((calling a train... but please please make note of where you are taking it if you are shouting it - and put it in say as well as shout for those who have shout off ))?<br>
<br>
Would you shout the praises of your god?  If you were in a place not friendly to that god?<br>
<br>
<br>
= = = = = = OOC observations:<br>
<br>
When shout was limited in range (to about the range of a shout in life vs the entire zone) it was -much- better and shouting was used in more RP ways than it is now in -some- zones, but it still can and should be used as an RP tool.<br>
<br>
You should -never- use shout to convey -anything- out of character.  <br>
<br>
If you hear a shouted question, answer that person in a tell or find them in person.  If you start a conversation, take it to /tell or /say or /group, etc.  <br>
<br>
Use shout sparingly and think about your in character reasons for doing so.  <br>
<br>
= = = = =<br>
<br>
I hope this helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-Caillou Kyrielle<br>
Bippin's betrothed<br>
