 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 1013<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 3:28:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2790.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: One other use for shout...</span><hr size=1> I will shout in towns for a bind, if I am evil and cannot walk to the soulbinder.  I don't consider it bad, but you have to remember not to spam people!  I'll do a /who periodically, and if it's the same people in the zone, I more than likely won't shout, since odds are they either have shout off or can't/won't help me.<br>
